":"Waterford, County Waterford, Irska"},"cs":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–po 1224","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Zesnulý","1190–Female":"1190–Zesnulá","1205–Male":"1205–Zesnulý","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"před 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"okolo 1205","after 1224":"po 1224","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Irsko","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Irsko","Ireland":"Irsko","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. Waterford, Ireland":"Waterford, County Waterford, Irsko"},"da":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–efter 1224","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Afdød","1190–Female":"1190–Afdød","1205–Male":"1205–Afdød","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"før 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"omkring 1205","after 1224":"efter 1224","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Irland","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Irland","Ireland":"Irland","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. Waterford, Ireland":"Waterford, County Waterford, Irland"},"nl":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–na 1224","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Overleden","1190–Female":"1190–Overleden","1205–Male":"1205–Overleden","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"vóór 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"circa 1205","after 1224":"na 1224","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Ierland","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Ierland","Ireland":"Ierland","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. Waterford, Ireland":"Waterford, County Waterford, Ierland"},"en":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–after 1224","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Deceased","1190–Female":"1190–Deceased","1205–Male":"1205–Deceased","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"before 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"about 1205","after 1224":"after 1224","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Ireland","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Ireland","Ireland":"Ireland","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. Waterford, Ireland":"Waterford, County Waterford, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"le","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Thanh, Hung, Minh, Dung, Tuan, Hai, Hoa, Thuy, Son, Anh, Long, Hoang.  Chinese Hong, Sang, Chi, Dong, Tong, Lai, Hang, Man, Han, Ho, Phoung, Chan.  Korean Tam, Phong, Nam, Thai, Tuong, Chung, Thach, Tinh, Manh, Tham, Uyen, Vang.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 樂, meaning ‘happiness’ in Chinese: from the first element of the personal name Le Fu (樂父), style name of Yan, son of the Duke Dai of Song (ruler of the state of Song, reigned 799–766  BC ). Yan's grandson Le Ju (樂莒) inherited Le (樂) as his surname.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 勒: (i) from the second element of the placename Shu-Le (疏勒), an ancient state (located in present-day Xinjiang Uyghur autonomous region) during the Western Han dynasty (206  BC –25  AD ). (ii) a surname near the Bohai Sea region during the Han dynasty (206  BC –220  AD ). (iii) a surname traced back to the Hun ethnic group in northern China during the Jin dynasty (265–420  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Yue","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Chi, Feng, Gang, Wei, Chun, Guo, Jin, Kin, Ping, Yan, Yun, Zhang, Chau, Du, Hau, Hung, My, Sau.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 岳 (or 嶽), meaning ‘high mountain’ in Chinese: traced back to Si Yue (四岳 or 四嶽), said to be the title of an official post in charge of sacrificial rituals on the site of famous mountains during the reign of the legendary Emperor Yao (<i>c.</i> 24th century  BC ) and Emperor Shun (<i>c.</i> 23rd century  BC )."]},{"name":"Lok","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Ping, Tat, Wing, Ying Lin, Chi Ming, Ching Wah, Chun, Chung Man, Han, Kam, Kam Tim, Kin.","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surname 樂, see   Le   1.","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surnames 陸, 鹿, 逯 and 禄, see   Lu   5 and (7-9)."]},{"name":"Li","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Ming, Li, Jian, Hong, Yan, Ping, Jing, Yong, Ying, Hui, Jin, Min, Chung.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 李, meaning ‘plum’: (i) said to have been adopted in place of the Chinese surname 理 (also pronounced Li; meaning ‘rules’ in Chinese) by Li Zhen (利貞), son of an official called Li Zheng (理徵) in the late Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). It is said that Li Zhen's father incurred the displeasure of King Zhou of Shang (died 1046  BC ) and Li Zhen fled to a wasteland area, where he survived on wild plums. After his return to civilization, he changed his surname to Li (李 ‘plum’), a word with the same pronunciation. The original surname, 理, is said to be from Li Guan (理官), the name of a post of officials in charge of legislation in ancient China. Li Er (李耳), also known as Lao Tzu or Lao Zi, traditionally regarded as the founder of Taoism, is believed to have been a descendant of Li Zhen. (ii) adopted as a surname by the Chi Li (叱李) family from the Xianbei ethnic group during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) in the early years of the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ), sixteen high officials with different surnames were granted the surname Li (李), the surname of the royal family of the Tang dynasty, by Emperor Taizong of Tang (died 649  BC ), because of their contributions to the establishment of the Tang regime. (iv) the surname can also be traced back to several minority ethnic groups in ancient China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 黎, meaning ‘black’ or ‘multitude’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from Li (黎), the name of an ancient state (located in Changzhi in Shanxi province) during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ), which was annexed in the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ) and later granted to Fengshu, also known as Li Hou (黎侯, 'Marquis Li'). (ii) adopted as a surname by the Su Li (素黎) family, members of the Xianbei ethnic group, during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD )."]}]},{"name":"Poher","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Siobhan.","Irish (western County Waterford and eastern County Cork): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Mochair</b> ‘descendant of <i>Mochar</i>’, from <i>mochar</i> ‘place overgrown with brushwood’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter le Poher was born in 1184, in Waterford, County Waterford, Ireland, his father, Robert le Poher, was 19 and his mother, Katherine Le Poer, was 15. He married Feya d'Eincourt before 1205, in Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1224, in his hometown."},"et":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–pärast 1224","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Surnud","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"enne 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"umbes 1205","after 1224":"pärast 1224","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Iirimaa","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. Waterford, Ireland":"Waterford, County Waterford, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–1224 jälkeen","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Kuollut","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"ennen vuotta 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"noin 1205","after 1224":"1224 jälkeen","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Irlanti","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. Waterford, Ireland":"Waterford, County Waterford, Irlanti"},"fr":{"1184–after 1224":"1184–après 1224","1184–1224":"1184–1224","1188–1260":"1188–1260","1188–Male":"1188–Décédé","1190–Female":"1190–Décédée","1205–Male":"1205–Décédé","1165–1188":"1165–1188","1169–1198":"1169–1198","1190":"1190","before 1205":"avant 1205","1198":"1198","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1260":"1260","1205":"1205","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","circa 1205":"environ 1205","after 1224":"après 1224","Wells, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Wells, County Kilkenny, Irlande","County Waterford, Eire":"County Waterford, Irlande","Ireland":"Irlande","Donoyle Castle, Donoyle, Kilmayden, Co. W